The original recipe turns out soft and fluffy. This is kind of funny. Once in home economics class we had to make cupcakes. We had to line up to use the scales to weigh our dry ingredients. I poured mine in too soon when another girl was using it. So it ended up with double the dry ingredients. The teacher was a terror and made me us it. So mine turned into rock cakes.

After the teacher checked them to grade I threw them out. The teacher half heartedly went off on me for wasting stuff. I was like feel free to take them out and eat them. She shut up and tried to suppress her laughter.
